parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty ignition switch can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to stalling, fires, and other safety issues.
Unstable idle and stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and safety risks.
Electrical system failures can lead to fires, stalling, and other safety issues.
Faulty computer modules can cause stalling, loss of control, and safety risks.
Battery failure can cause stalling, loss of power, and safety risks.
The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected loss of power and potential accidents.
An engine compartment fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden engine compartment fire without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause engine damage, overheating, and stalling, leading to unexpected loss of power and potential accidents.
The failure of the exhaust system can cause noise, vibration, and potentially lead to carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: Tail pipe rusting and falling off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause loose or excessive steering wheel movement, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel has a lot of movement
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the rack and pinion assembly needs to be repaired or replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fire in the steering column can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system, potentially leading to a loss of control or a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire in the area of the steering column

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering belt can cause a loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering system is inoperable.
